      "message": "The order of x/xy may also matter:\n\nCombinedShannonEntropy_C - Here\u0027s X first.\n\n    if (x !\u003d 0) {\n      const int xy \u003d x + Y[i];\n      sumX +\u003d x;\n      retval -\u003d VP8LFastSLog2(x);\n      sumXY +\u003d xy;\n      retval -\u003d VP8LFastSLog2(xy);\n    } else if (Y[i] !\u003d 0) {\n      sumXY +\u003d Y[i];\n      retval -\u003d VP8LFastSLog2(Y[i]);\n    }\n\nCombinedShannonEntropy_SSE2 - but here I\u0027m copied from the WebP2, where\u0027s XY first:\n\n      const int32_t j \u003d BitsCtz(my);\n      const int xy \u003d X[i + j] + Y[i + j];\n      sumX +\u003d xy;\n      retval -\u003d VP8LFastSLog2(xy);\n      if ((mx \u003e\u003e j) \u0026 1) {\n        const int x \u003d X[i + j];\n        sumXY +\u003d x;\n        retval -\u003d VP8LFastSLog2(x);\n      }\n\nSo better is to swap X and XY to match C reference code:\n\n      const int32_t j \u003d BitsCtz(my);\n      if ((mx \u003e\u003e j) \u0026 1) {\n        const int x \u003d X[i + j];\n        sumXY +\u003d x;\n        retval -\u003d VP8LFastSLog2(x);\n      }\n      const int xy \u003d X[i + j] + Y[i + j];\n      sumX +\u003d xy;\n      retval -\u003d VP8LFastSLog2(xy);",
